Samuel arap Yego, News24 correspondent iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - A controversial Kenyan businessman, Jacob Juma, has been short dead in Nairobi .Juma was shot dead on Thursday night by unknown gunmen as he drove towards his home in Karen.Confirming the incident, Nairobi Criminal Investigations Department (CID) boss, Ireri Kamwende, said the businessman was gunned down around 21:30.Kamwende said the thugs escaped on a motorcycle after spraying the businessman's car with&nbsp;more than&nbsp;10 bullets. The thugs did not steal anything from Juma, a bitter critic of the Jubilee government and close ally of Cord leader Raila Odinga. His death was likely to raise concerns that it was politically motivated if his controversial posts on Facebook and Twitter bashing president Uhuru Kenyatta's government were anything to go by 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.